'''Wakamiya-sha''' (若宮社) refers to Shinto shrines across Japan. Some are distinguished by additional place names.
* {{ill|Iwashimizu Hachiman Shrine|ja|石清水八幡宮}} subsidiary shrine - Kyoto Prefecture, Yawata City; shrine building designated as an Important Cultural Property. * {{ill|Yoshida Shrine|ja|吉田神社}} subsidiary shrine - Kyoto Prefecture, Kyoto City, Sakyo Ward. * {{ill|Ōmiwa Shrine|ja|大神神社}} subsidiary shrine; another name for {{ill|Ōtataneko Shrine|ja|大直禰子神社}} - Nara Prefecture, Sakurai City. * {{ill|Hiro Hachiman Shrine|ja|広八幡神社}} subsidiary shrine - Wakayama Prefecture, Hirogawa Town; shrine building designated as an Important Cultural Property. * {{ill|Wakamiya-sha (Gosen)|ja|若宮社（五泉市)}} - Niigata Prefecture, Gosen City. * {{ill|Suzumemori Wakamiya-sha|ja|雀森若宮社}} - Niigata Prefecture, Tsubame City. * {{ill|Wakamiya-sha (Okazaki)|ja|若宮社 (岡崎市)}} - Aichi Prefecture, Okazaki City. * {{ill|Hakusan Shrine (Heguri)|ja|白山神社 (平群町)}} subsidiary shrine - Nara Prefecture, Heguri Town. * {{ill|Chinjyu Wakamiya-sha|ja|鎮守若宮社}} - Ehime Prefecture, Matsuyama City. * {{ill|Wakamiya-sha (Saga)|ja|若宮社 (佐賀市)}} - Saga Prefecture, Saga City. * {{ill|Wakamiya-sha (Usa)|ja|若宮社 (宇佐市)}} - Ōita Prefecture, Usa City. == See Also == * [[若宮|Wakamiya (disambiguation)]] * [[若宮神社|Wakamiya Shrine (disambiguation)]] * [[若宮八幡宮|Wakamiya Hachiman-gū (disambiguation)]]
